ntial. I wonder if the generated tests can do without compile-time annotations? Including Swagger annotations is a must. There's a possibility I might need the dependency `tools.jackson.core:jackson-databind:3.0.2` if I require the JsonNode type. The jsonschema-generator may already include it for me, so I shouldn't add it separately. I should check my setup regarding org.assertj and assertions too!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying test guidance**\\n\\nI want to ensure that for the test setup guidance, it's important to specify that there should be \\\"No env/system properties\\\" referenced. If my tests are using the generated schema node type on version 5.x, I should use `tools.jackson.databind.JsonNode` from Jackson 3 as provided through the jsonschema-generator, not the `com.fasterxml` version. Also, the \\\"agent_guidance\\\" needs to explicitly mention adding environment variables, system properties, and other test-code setup. That's key to follow!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"Meaningful tests require the provided-scope companion generator and Swagger annotation APIs; the module is only an add-on and its POM does not transitively provide those classes to the test scaffold.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"com.github.victools:jsonschema-generator:5.0.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The module POM declares jsonschema-generator with provided scope, while normal usage constructs a SchemaGenerator and registers Swagger2Module; version 5.0.0 documentation recommends aligned generator/module versions.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"io.swagger.core.v3:swagger-annotations:2.2.41\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The module POM declares swagger-annotations with provided scope, and meaningful coverage requires io.swagger.v3 annotations such as @Schema/@ArraySchema on test model classes; 2.2.41 is the version managed by the 5.0.0 parent.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No Docker image, environment variable, or system property is needed. For 5.x tests, use the Jackson 3 node type returned by the generator, e.g. tools.jackson.databind.JsonNode, and register new Swagger2Module() with SchemaGeneratorConfigBuilder before generating schemas.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Reusing 4.x test imports such as com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.JsonNode will cause javac failures because jsonschema-generator 5.0.0 uses Jackson 3 packages.\",\n    \"If the provided-scope dependencies are omitted, generated tests may compile only shallow module instantiation or fail to resolve SchemaGenerator, JsonNode, or Swagger annotation types.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0f1ed7931fb2349e016a405b2eb0748194bff8e8fb959922d8\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1746, "output": 1431, "cacheRead": 18944, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 22121, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782602528410, "responseId": "resp_0f1ed7931fb2349e016a405b2110348194adc63bbf783ef9cd"}}
